      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALL OVER IT (1) saluted two runs back then recorded an effortless victory last time out, scoring by 11 metres over 1690m at this track. Has the benefit of a good draw. Has won all of his three career runs. Meeting a deeper field this time but he has the ability to mix it with them. MIDNIGHT MOTH (5) saluted two runs back then things went sour last time when he broke and finished 18 metres back in fourth over 1650m at Bendigo after leading at the bell. Needs to get it right to beat this field but he is up to the job. ROCKNROLL WISH NZ (4) is the next elect off a last-start win by 7 metres at Bendigo over 1650m when fresh from a spell. Has won all of his last three runs. SECRET SERVICE AGENT NZ (3) must be considered after he finished runner-up when resuming over 1650m at Bendigo a week-and-a-half ago. He has placed in all of his last four runs.",
